This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as object detection and instance segmentation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and modifications to CNNs, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also discusses the use of Hough voting, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.GR (computer graphics) and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, and cs.NE.
